{"title":"New Orbea Laufey has aggressive geometry and internal frame storage in its LOCKR","link":"https://www.bikeradar.com/news/2024-orbea-laufey/","date":1697724028000,"content":"<img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2023/10/Orbea-laufey-2024-Large1-628b10a.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=620,413\" srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2023/10/Orbea-laufey-2024-Large1-628b10a.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=2400,1598 2400w, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2023/10/Orbea-laufey-2024-Large1-628b10a.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1920,1278 1920w, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2023/10/Orbea-laufey-2024-Large1-628b10a.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1440,959 1440w, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2023/10/Orbea-laufey-2024-Large1-628b10a.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1200,799 1200w, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2023/10/Orbea-laufey-2024-Large1-628b10a.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=960,639 960w, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2023/10/Orbea-laufey-2024-Large1-628b10a.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=720,479 720w, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2023/10/Orbea-laufey-2024-Large1-628b10a.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=576,383 576w, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2023/10/Orbea-laufey-2024-Large1-628b10a.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=360,239 360w, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2023/10/Orbea-laufey-2024-Large1-628b10a.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=180,119 180w\" width=\"620\" height=\"413\" alt=\"Orbea Laufey being ridden downhill in woods.\" title=\"Orbea Laufey being ridden downhill in woods.\" />                                            <p>Orbea has launched its new Laufey, with updated geometry, a revised frame and a 140mm fork.</p>\n<p>The new <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/advice/buyers-guides/best-hardtail-mountain-bikes/\">hardtail</a> will be available in three models, all sharing the same aluminium frame.</p>\n<p>The Laufey starts at £1,599 / $1,899 / $1,499 for the H30 model, which features a <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/advice/buyers-guides/rockshox-suspension-fork-guide/\">RockShox Recon RL</a> fork, while the top-of-the-range H-LTD model is priced at £2,699 / $2,999 / €2,499 and sees a <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/advice/buyers-guides/fox-suspension-fork-guide/\">Fox 34 Float Performance</a> up-front.</p>\n<p>Orbea says the bikes are available to order now through its website.</p>\n<h2>Sleek new silhouette</h2>\n<div>\n    \n        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n    \n    <img width=\"620\" height=\"413\" alt=\"Orbea Laufey pac shot\" title=\"Orbea Laufey pac shot\" />\n\n</div><div><figcaption><span><i></i> Orbea says the Laufey has been designed for everything from cross-country to jumpy local trails.</span></figcaption><span> <i>Orbea</i></span></div>\n<p>The Laufey frame now has a more aggressive-looking sloping top tube that helps create the illusion of a straight line from the headset to the rear axle.</p>\n<p>Alongside this, the front triangle features Orbea’s Steep’n’Deep seat tube, which is said to enable you to slam the saddle completely out of the way for descents and welcome long-travel <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/advice/buyers-guides/best-dropper-posts/\">dropper posts</a>.</p>\n<div>\n    \n        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n    \n    <img width=\"620\" height=\"413\" alt=\"Orbea Laufey with LOCKR\" title=\"Orbea Laufey with LOCKR\" />\n\n</div><div><figcaption><span><i></i> The LOCKR panel also has mounts for a bottle cage.</span></figcaption><span> <i>Orbea</i></span></div>\n<p>The new frame also features the brand’s LOCKR internal storage seen on the new <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/reviews/bikes/mountain-bikes/full-suspension-mountain-bikes/orbea-occam-lt-m10/\">Orbea Occam LT</a>, which gives you access to the down tube to store tools and accessories.</p>\n<p>Like the <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/news/orbea-laufey-2020/\">previous Laufey</a>, the new bike continues to use a 140mm fork on the front and has room for 2.6in tyres for added bump absorption.</p>\n<p>Orbea has given the Laufey internal cable routing to minimise rubbing and rattling, and there’s an ISCG01 mount on the bottom bracket, meaning you can add a chain guide.</p>\n<h2>Ready to rock geometry</h2>\n<div>\n    \n        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n    \n    <img width=\"620\" height=\"413\" alt=\"Orbea Laufey pac shot\" title=\"Orbea Laufey pac shot\" />\n\n</div><div><figcaption><span><i></i> Orbea offers the Laufey in four sizes: S, M, L and XL.</span></figcaption><span> <i>Orbea</i></span></div>\n<p>The Laufey has been given a ‘Ready to Rock’ geometry, which Orbea says means the bike will cope with anything you can throw at it.</p>\n<p>With a head angle of 64.5 degrees, the new bike is one degree slacker than the previous Laufey.</p>\n<p>The seat tube angles have steepened from 75 degrees to 77 degrees, while chainstay lengths increase from 435mm to 440mm.</p>\n<p>Reach measurements are up 2mm to 475mm on a size-large frame, which should make the bike feel more stable.</p>\n<div>\n                <table>\n                <colgroup>\n                            <col></col>\n                            <col></col>\n                            <col></col>\n                            <col></col>\n                            <col></col>\n                    </colgroup>\n        <thead>\n<tr>\n                                                                                        <th></th><th>S</th><th>M</th><th>L</th><th>XL</th></tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n\n        <tr>\n            <td><b> Seat tube </b> (mm)</td><td>380</td><td>415</td><td>430</td><td>460</td>        </tr>\n            <tr>\n            <td><b>Top tube</b> (mm)</td><td>572</td><td>598</td><td>625</td><td>652</td>        </tr>\n            <tr>\n            <td><b>Head tube</b> (mm)</td><td>95</td><td>105</td><td>120</td><td>130</td>        </tr>\n            <tr>\n            <td><b>Chainstay</b> (mm)</td><td>440</td><td>440</td><td>440</td><td>440</td>        </tr>\n            <tr>\n            <td><b>BB height</b> (mm)</td><td>310</td><td>310</td><td>310</td><td>310</td>        </tr>\n            <tr>\n            <td><b>BB drop </b>(mm)</td><td>65</td><td>65</td><td>65</td><td>65</td>        </tr>\n            <tr>\n            <td><b>Wheelbase</b> (mm)</td><td>1,181.8</td><td>1,210.1</td><td>1,240.6</td><td>1,269.9</td>        </tr>\n            <tr>\n            <td><b>Head angle </b>(degrees)</td><td>64.5</td><td>64.5</td><td>64.5</td><td>64.5</td>        </tr>\n            <tr>\n            <td><b>Seat angle</b> (degrees)</td><td>77</td><td>77</td><td>77</td><td>77</td>        </tr>\n            <tr>\n            <td><b>Standover </b>(mm)</td><td>440</td><td>440</td><td>440</td><td>440</td>        </tr>\n            <tr>\n            <td><b>Reach</b> (mm)</td><td>427</td><td>451</td><td>475</td><td>500</td>        </tr>\n            <tr>\n            <td><b>Stack</b> (mm)</td><td>633</td><td>642</td><td>655.5</td><td>664.5</td>        </tr>\n            <tr>\n            <td><b>Fork length </b>(mm)</td><td>554</td><td>554</td><td>554</td><td>554</td>        </tr>\n            <tr>\n            <td><b>Rake </b>(mm)</td><td>44</td><td>44</td><td>44</td><td>44</td>        </tr>\n    </tbody>\n    </table>\n                    \n                                \n                                \n                                \n                                \n                \n    \n    \n</div>\n\n<h2>Orbea Laufey specs and pricing</h2>\n<h3>Orbea Laufey H30</h3>\n<div>\n    \n        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n    \n    <img width=\"620\" height=\"413\" alt=\"Orbea Laufey H30\" title=\"Orbea Laufey H30\" />\n\n</div><div><figcaption><span><i></i> All models come equipped with a dropper post.</span></figcaption><span> <i>Orbea</i></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fork:</strong> RockShox Recon RL, 140mm</li>\n<li><strong>Drivetrain:</strong> Shimano Deore M6100</li>\n<li><strong>Brakes:</strong> Shimano MT201</li>\n<li><strong>Wheels:</strong> Unbranded alloy, tubeless</li>\n<li><strong>Tyres:</strong> Maxxis Dissector, 2.6in</li>\n<li><strong>Price:</strong> £1,599 / $1,899 / $1,499</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Orbea Laufey H10</h3>\n<div>\n    \n        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n    \n    <img width=\"620\" height=\"413\" alt=\"Orbea Laufey H10\" title=\"Orbea Laufey H10\" />\n\n</div><div><figcaption><span><i></i> There are mounts under the top tube for a cage or accessories.</span></figcaption><span> <i>Orbea</i></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fork:</strong> Marzocchi Bomber Z2, 140mm</li>\n<li><strong>Drivetrain:</strong> Shimano SLX M7100</li>\n<li><strong>Brakes:</strong> Shimano M6100</li>\n<li><strong>Wheels:</strong> Unbranded alloy, tubeless</li>\n<li><strong>Tyres:</strong> Maxxis Dissector, 2.6in</li>\n<li><strong>Price:</strong> £2,099 / $2,499 / $1,899</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Orbea Laufey H-LTD</h3>\n<div>\n    \n        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n    \n    <img width=\"620\" height=\"413\" alt=\"Orbea Laufey H-LTD\" title=\"Orbea Laufey H-LTD\" />\n\n</div><div><figcaption><span><i></i> Orbea matches the Fox decals to the secondary colour of the frame.</span></figcaption><span> <i>Orbea</i></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fork:</strong> Fox 34 Float Performance, 140mm</li>\n<li><strong>Drivetrain:</strong> Shimano XT M8100</li>\n<li><strong>Brakes:</strong> Shimano M6120</li>\n<li><strong>Wheels:</strong> Race Face AR 30c</li>\n<li><strong>Tyres:</strong> Maxxis Dissector, 2.6in</li>\n<li><strong>Price:</strong> £2,699 / $2,999 / €2,499</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>","author":"Nick Clark","siteTitle":"BikeRadar","siteHash":"df99dd1320fcd97327a2def4c67247c08cd4090a7dab684a0eddb9b856f80ef1","entryHash":"8de55fd669893269ecd1b33ebe725743eefaf14d0dcc5d91c3092fc5edfe1012","category":"Cycling"}